  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Extractives and Development</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="DE">Sektorvorhaben Rohstoffe und Entwicklung (BGR Modul)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="DE">Das Sektorprogramm Rohstoffe und Entwicklung ber&#xE4;t das
        Bundesministerium f&#xFC;r wirtschaftliche Zusammenarbeit und Entwicklung und entwickelt Ans&#xE4;tze
        f&#xFC;r die deutsche Entwicklungszusammenarbeit im Rohstoffsektor. Schwerpunkte der Arbeit des
        Programms umfassen die wirtschaftliche Entwicklung in rohstoffreichen Partnerl&#xE4;ndern, die
        Einhaltung von Menschenrechten, Umwelt- und Sozialstandards, die St&#xE4;rkung von Institutionen
        in Partnerl&#xE4;ndern sowie die Themen Reduktion von Gas Flaring und Rohstoffe f&#xFC;r die
        Energiewende.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The sector program Extractives and Development provides advice to the
        Federal Ministery for Economic Cooperation and Development and develops new approaches for
        German Development Cooperation in the field of mining. Core areas of work include the
        economic development of resource rich partner countries, human rights, compliance with
        environmental and social standards, institutional capacity building as well as the field of
        energy resources, particularly regarding the reduction of gas flaring and the commodities
        needed to pursue the transition towards green energy production.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="DE">Die deutsche Entwicklungszusammenarbeit wendet bedarfsorientierte,
        geb&#xFC;ndelte L&#xF6;sungsans&#xE4;tze zur F&#xF6;rderung der Nachhaltigkeit im Rohstoffsektor in
        Entwicklungs- und Schwellenl&#xE4;ndern an und vertritt ihre Politikziele im nationalen und
        internationalen Politikdialog.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The sector program Extractives and Development provides advice to the
        Federal Ministery for Economic Cooperation and Development and develops new approaches for
        German Development Cooperation in the field of mining. Core areas of work include the
        economic development of resource rich partner countries, human rights, compliance with
        environmental and social standards, institutional capacity building as well as the field of
        energy resources, particularly regarding the reduction of gas flaring and the commodities
        needed to pursue the transition towards green energy production.</narrative>
  </description>
